### Setup

* $\pi\colon E\to X$ a holomorphic rank-$r$ bundle;
* $f\colon F_k\to X$ the bundle of $(r-k+1)$-frames of $E$ _along with a choice of complement_, with fibre $W_k$ _homotopic_ to the Stiefel manifold $W_k^n$;
* the Deligne complex $$\mathbb{Z}(p)=(2\pi i)^p\mathbb{Z}\hookrightarrow\mathcal{O}_X\xrightarrow{\d}\Omega_X^1\xrightarrow{\d}\ldots\xrightarrow{\d}\Omega_X^{p-1}$$ where $(2\pi i)^p\mathbb{Z}$ is in degree zero;
* sheaves (because we sheafify them) $\mathscr{F}_p$ on $X$ for $p\in\{0,\ldots,2k\}$ where $$\mathscr{F}_p(U)=\{\sigma\colon U\times\Delta^p\to U\times W_k\cong f^{-1}(U) \mid f\sigma(x,t)=x\}\text{ ;}$$
* _homologically-graded_ complex $$\mathscr{T}_\bullet = \mathbb{Z}_X\hookrightarrow\mathscr{F}_{2k-1}\big/\mathscr{F}_{2k}\xrightarrow{\partial}\mathscr{F}_{2k-2}\xrightarrow{\partial}\ldots\xrightarrow{\partial}\mathscr{F}_0$$ where $\mathscr{F}_0$ is in degree zero and $\partial$ is the usual boundary operator from the singular chain complex; the inclusion of $\mathbb{Z}$ into $(\mathscr{F}_{2k-1}/\mathscr{F}_{2k})(U)$ comes from the fact that kernel (under $\partial$) of the latter calculates the singular homology of $W_k$, which we know to be isomorphic to $\mathbb{Z}$;
* more generally, the local homology (i.e. the homology of a chain complex) is exactly the singular homology of the fibre, i.e. $$\mathscr{H}_i(\mathscr{T}_\bullet)\cong\H_i(W_k;\mathbb{Z})\text{ for }i\in\{1,\ldots,2k-1\}$$ and so $\mathscr{T}_\bullet$ is exact _except_ at degree zero, giving us a quasi-isomorphism $$\mathscr{T}_\bullet\xrightarrow{\sim}\mathbb{Z}_X[0]\text{ ;}$$
* we have an element $\tau\in\mathbb{H}^0(X;\mathscr{T}_\bullet)$ corresponding to $1\in\mathbb{Z}$ under the following chain of isomorphisms: $$\mathbb{Z}\cong\H^0(W_k;\mathbb{Z})\cong\mathbb{H}^0(W_k;\mathbb{Z}_X[0])\cong\mathbb{H}^0(X;\mathscr{T}_\bullet).$$
